- Tue 16 Jul 2019. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited] https://mailchi.mp/sante.gouv.cd/ebola_kivu_16juil19?e=f96cddba3b

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 15 Jul 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 2512, 2418 confirmed and 94 probable. In total, there have been 1676 deaths (1582 in confirmed and 94 in probable cases) and 703 people have recovered;
- 423 suspected cases under investigation;
- 11 new confirmed cases, including 5 in Beni [North Kivu], 2 in Mandima [Ituri], 1 in Mabalako [North Kivu], 1 in Vuhovi [Ituri], 1 in Katwa [North Kivu], and 1 in Komanda [Ituri];
- 8 new deaths of confirmed cases, including 3 community deaths -- 2 in Beni and 1 in Mandima; 5 ETC/TC deaths -- 4 in Beni and 1 in Goma [North Kivu];
- 3 recoveries released from ETCs -- 2 in Butembo and 1 in Katwa [North Kivu].

News
Follow-up of the situation of the contacts of the pastor who traveled to Goma
---------------------------------------------------------------------
- On Mon 15 Jul 2019, 37 high-risk contacts and 40 contacts of the contacts of the Goma confirmed case were vaccinated at the Afia Himbi Health Center where the patient had been isolated before being transferred to the ETC. In total, 97 contacts in the broad sense have already been listed to date. Vaccination will continue until all identified contacts have been vaccinated.
- Among the contacts identified were 2 women from the pastor's family traveling with him. After the pastor's transfer to the ETC, they hid in Goma and some people thought they had fled to Bukavu in South Kivu province. Fortunately, the 2 women were found in Goma on Tue 16 Jul 2019 and will be vaccinated.

