"We commend @WHO for making this tough decision, it is right to do so. Over 1600 people have died already, with children accounting for around 1/3 of cases. The teams in DRC deserve all our thanks, respect, and support." - Josie Golding, epidemics lead

"There is a grave risk of a major increase in numbers, or spread to new locations -- as we've seen this week in Goma, again in Uganda and recently close to the border of South Sudan."

"The calling of a PHEIC is an opportunity for a change in the response to help stop Ebola spreading and save lives. A step-up in the response, led by the DRC and with full international support, is critical if we are to bring the epidemic to an end."

"This must include enhanced diplomatic, public health, security, and logistic efforts as well as releasing much needed financial resources. There is also a pressing need to introduce a second vaccine in the DRC to protect communities outside of the current outbreak zone."

"Countries should not wait for Ebola to spread across borders or appear on their doorstep before acting." @BeakerH #OutsmartEpidemics

